.cm
 
     Invocation:  FPADMIN <filepool name>
 
                          <filepool name> default is VMPSxx where xx
                                          is the last 2 chars of nodename
 
     Usage:
 
     To make admin tasks easier by using a panel driven tool.
     Under the cover the normal SFS filepool administration commands are used.
     See: HELP SFSADMIN MENU and HELP CMS MENU for the commands and
          their correct syntax
 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
     "Main" panel:
 
     Displays all filespaces found on the filepool.
     When there is ADMIN behind one of the filespaces this user id is
     enrolled as ADMIN as well for the filepool.
 
     PF-keys:
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 1 Help     | Displays Help                                               |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 2 Stats    | Shows some statistics (QUERY FILEPOOL MINIDISK)             |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 3 Quit     | Exits from the tool                                         |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 4 Zoom     | Zooms in on more details of the filespace                   |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 5 Enroll   | Enroll a new user on the filepool,                          |
    |            | the new user id must exist                                  |
    |            | Enter the name on the command line and pref the PF-key      |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 6 Admin    | Toggles the ADMIN status of the user id                     |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 7          |                                                             |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 8          |                                                             |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 9 DelUsr   | Remove a user from the filepool, put the cursor on the line |
    |            | containing the user that needs to be removed and            |
    |            | hit the PF-k                                                |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    |10 ListUgs  | List the usage of the filepool per filespace                |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    |11 List     | Display the content of the filespace (FILELIST)             |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    |12 Quit     | Exits from the tool                                         |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
 
     "Zoom" panel:
 
     Displays details for filespace and directories for the selected user id.
     Details are directory type (DIRCONTROL/FILECONTROL) and authorizations.
 
     PF-keys:
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 1 Help     : Displays Help                                               |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 2 Conflict : Shows if there are conflicts for this filespace             |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 3 Return   : Returns to the Main panel                                   |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 4 ModAut   : Modify authorisations(GRANT or REVOKE)                      |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 5 Grant    : Grant a user access to this filespace                       |
    |            | Enter the userid and authorisations on the command line     |
    |            | and hit the PF-key                                          |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 6 DirAttr  : Toggles the directory type (FILECONTROL <> DIRCONTROL)      |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 7          |                                                             |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 8          |                                                             |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    | 9 Revoke   : Revoke a user id from this filespace                        |
    |            | Enter the userid on the command line and press the PF-key   |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    |10 Display the content of the filespace/directory (FILELIST)              |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    |11 List     : Display the content of the filespace/directory (FILELIST)   |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
    |12 Quit     : Exits from FPADMIN                                          |
    +------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
